@ENDNODE

@NODE GENERAL "2.1 General"
@{b}@{u}2.1 General@{uu}@{ub}

@{u}Start of XTrace :@{uu}

To start XTrace just double click its icon or type its program name in a
shell window. Further assigns, pathes or stack values are @{b}not@{ub} necessary.

@{u}Operator's finish messages :@{uu}

Operations which do change a picture, show their results in a requester
when finished. The picture can be displayed by selecting "Display Gray"
or "Display Color". Optionally you can select "Undo", "Undo & Redo" and
"Redo". With "Ok" you do accept the changed picture.

According to the operator and settings it is possible some functions are not
available, for example "Undo" and "Undo & Redo" if you have deactivated
Undo in the @{"settings" link MENU_SETGENERAL } respectively there was no free memory for undo,
and/or "Redo" if it is without sense and/or "Color Display" if the actual
operator only available for pictures with the @{"Color-Typ" link XTrace_Appendix.guide/GLOSSARY } "Gray" or "B/W".

@{b}Undo isn't available after "Ok" is selected!@{ub} 

@{u}Cycle-Gadgets :@{uu}

Because I use in XTrace exclusively cycle gadgets and no MX gadgets, I
suggest for easier usage of XTrace, to use a background program which can
patch the cycle gadgets for lists with all contained entries.

For example you can use "CycleToMenu" by F. Giannici (Cardware; Aminet) or
"MCP" (since V1.20; Mailware; Aminet) by AlienDesign.

@{u}Ok- and Cancel gadgets :@{uu}

These gadgets can also be used with the <ESC> key for "Cancel" and the
<Return> key for "Ok".
@ENDNODE

